the president (or their designee) may temporarily assign an employee to a position in a higher classification or may temporarily reclassify an employee for the performance of duties in a higher classification. the president (or their designee) may temporarily elevate an employee’s skill level through a temporary in-class progression for the performance of duties at a higher skill level in the same or a different position. an employee shall be provided with written notice of such a temporary assignment of duties of another classification or temporary in class progression at least seven (7) days prior to the effective date. to request a temporary reassignment submit the following to onboarding@sjsu.edu : employees may be permanently reassigned to another position in the same classification and skill level as the employee’s existing classification and skill level. an employee shall be provided written notice of permanent reassignment to another position fourteen (14) days prior to the effective date of such a reassignment. to request a permanent reassignment submit the following to onboarding@sjsu.edu : university-personnel@sjsu.edu up north: 408-924-2450 up south: 408-924-2250  up webmaster up north administration building 242 up south upd building 3rd floor 